The paper deals with entity linking, which is a task in natural language processing (NLP) that involves linking mentions of entities in text to their corresponding entries in a knowledge base. This task is closely related to several sub-fields of NLP, such as computational linguistics (CL), information retrieval (IR), and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are a popular machine learning technique that has been applied to a wide range of problems in computer science, including NLP. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CL, which covers topics related to NLP and CL. Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (which covers topics related to IR), cs.AI (which covers topics related to AI), cs.LG (which covers topics related to machine learning), and cs.NE (which covers topics related to neural networks).
